$interpreted: Lio: Uhhhh...where is this? What are you guys going to do?
Ragdoll Coroner: Bad children must be punished! RARGH!!.
Lio: Waah!!
Lio: Flutterfly?
Lio: Alright Flutterfly, help me open a path!
Lio: Flutterfly, run, now!
Ragdoll Coroner: Bad boy ~ RAAARGH!!!
Lio: Hey, is somebody there? Please come out, help!
Lio: The thing behind me is the culprit who murdered Eugene. Get him now!
Hyacinthus: What did you just say!?
Nigel: How is that possible...
Hyacinthus: What is that...it doesn't feel like a human or a monster. AllI feel is an immense sense of bitterness and hatred...
Hyacinthus: Could it be that the legend of the Ragdoll Coroner is true?
Nigel: Don't speak such nonsense. There must be a reasonable explanation for all of this, including the way it just vanished...
Hyacinthus: Well...what is it...
Nigel: How would I know, but I'll see what I can find. Go check on Lio to make sure he's alright.
Hyacinthus: Are you hurt? Why would you run outside the Slums during the middle of the night again?
Lio: Leah said that Nigel is a bad person. I didn't believe her, so I want to find the true culprit who murdered Eugene.
Lio: That way, I can prove Nigel's innocence.
Hyacinthus: No way in hell would Nigel murder Eugene. What would make you even think something like that?
Lio: Thank goodness. So all the bad things were done by the Ragdoll Coroner!
Nigel: Have no idea what you're talking about... Regardless, we should continue tomorrow. Everyone, return to the house. It's getting late.
Nigel: Thank you for believing me this time. I promise you, I will try my best to be a good person.
Lio: Hmm? What does that mean?
Nigel: Nothing. Go back to your room and sleep, ya little brat.
